# Wiring Notes

## Control Circuit

L → TC1 (NO) → TC2 (NC) → TS1 (NC) → KM1 (A1)
N → KM1 (A2)

## Power Circuit

L → KM1 (COM)
KM1 (NO) → Heater
N → Heater

## Key Design Rules

- Safety devices must be NC
- All safety devices in series
- Contactor isolates high voltage from control circuit

## Safety Checks

- Verify continuity of NC chain
- Test thermal cut-out manually
- Confirm contactor drops out on fault
